Ok...first I know how redit on, mset on, and whatever else is nice but
it seems to be crashing the mud. I dunno why or how yet, but all the
logs indicate that usually the only time the mud crashes is when one
of those editors is in the on position. So do your best to try to just
build without turning it on. Also I have some news concerning mobs. heh.
You can leave the following parts of the mob OUT when making a mob due
to the mud setting the default values for you:
 
hitroll, damroll, armor, hp, mana, move, practice.
 
That way you don't have to worry about numbers...only takes about 4 mins
per mob if that...
Take care,
